    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Genesis 49</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Gen049-P83v-L6_trl" n="6" prev="ADub.III.73.001.048.trl.xml#Gen048-P83v-L6_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And Jacob called
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            his sons, and said, ‘Assemble and let me tell you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            what will befall you in the last days.</l>
                        <l n="2">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            Assemble and listen, oh sons of Jacob,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            and listen to the words of Israel, your father.</l>
                        <l n="3">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            Reuben, you are my firstborn, my might, and the beginning of my strength,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            the fame of priesthood and the fame of reign.</l>
                        <l n="4">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            Recklessness like the flow of water is to be found in you, you will not
                            be famous,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            because you went up to your father’s bed, then you defiled,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            it was cut off |from you|.</l>
                        <l n="5">Simeon and Levi
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            are brothers: weapons of wickedness are in their habitations.</l>
                        <l n="6">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            My soul did not come into their secret, into their assembly,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            my spirit did not become united. For in their anger they killed a man,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            and they wilfully ruined a stronghold.</l>
                        <l n="7">Cursed is
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            their anger, for it is fierce, and their fury, for it is cruel.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            I will divide them in Jacob, and scatter them in Israel.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="84r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="8">Judah: You, your brothers will praise you. Your hand will be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            on the neck of your enemies, your father’s children will bow down before
                            you.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="9">Judah is a lion’s cub: from prey, my son,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            you are gone up. He kneeled down, he lay down as a lion, and as a lioness:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            who will rouse him?</l>
                        <l n="10">Reign will not depart
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            from Judah, or a statute-giver among his families, until
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            the Messiah comes, and to him will be the obedience of the peoples.</l>
                        <l n="11">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            He will tie his mule to the vine and his donkey’s colt to a thin branch,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            he will wash his garments in wine and his quilt in the blood of
                            grapes.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="12">The redness of his eyes will be because of the plenty
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            of wine, and the whiteness of his teeth will be because of the plenty of
                            milk.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="13">Zebulun will dwell at the haven of the seas, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            he shall be for a haven for ships, and his border shall be at Sidon.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                        <l n="14">Issachar is of thick bones, lies down
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            between two <supplied reason="lost">†cowsheds</supplied><ref
                                target="#fn1" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="15">And he saw rest, that it was good,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            and the land, that it was pleasant, and he bowed his shoulder to bear
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            the burden of reading the Law, and became a tribute-payer,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            instead of a servant.</l>
                        <l n="16">Dan will judge his people
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            as one of the tribes of Israel <seg type="commented" corresp="#seg001" />from
                            which Shimshon will come forth,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            and will be the judge of Israel<anchor type="commented" xml:id="seg001"
                                 /><ref target="#fn2" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="17">Dan will be like a serpent
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            by the road, like a viper by the path, that bites
                            <milestone unit="page" n="84v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            the horse’s heels, and its rider falls backward.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="18">I hope for your salvation, oh Lord.</l>
                        <l n="19">Gad,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            a troop gathers over him, but at the last he will gather
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            and overcome.</l>
                        <l n="20">About Asher: his food will be fat, and he
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            will yield a king’s heavenly food.</l>
                        <l n="21">Naphtali
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            is like a fawn <seg type="commented" corresp="#seg002" />let loose<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="seg002" /><ref target="#fn3"
                                type="noteAnchor" />, who gives pleasant words.</l>
                        <l n="22">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            Joseph is like a bough at full strength, a spreading bough by a well, thin
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            branches that strutted on a stronghold.</l>
                        <l n="23">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            the archers teased him, and shot at him, and were hostile to him.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="24">But his bow dwelt in strength, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            the arms of his hands were made strong by the strength of the mighty God
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            of Jacob, from there is the shepherd, the foundation of Israel,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                        <l n="25">by the command of God of your father, and he shall help you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            and by the mighty God, and he shall bless you with blessings of heavens
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            from the heavens above, with blessings of the deep that lies beneath,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            with blessings of the breasts and of the womb.</l>
                        <l n="26">The blessings
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            of your father have prevailed above the blessings of my parents
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            up to the tokens of the everlasting rocks. They shall be on the head of Joseph,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            and on the brow of the head of the one separate from his brothers.</l>
                        <l n="27">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            Benjamin will tear up like a wolf, in the morning he will devour the
                            cattle, and at night
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            he will divide the spoil.’</l>
                        <l n="28">All these are the twelve tribes of Israel:
                            <milestone unit="page" n="85r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            and this is it what their father spoke to them, and he blessed them.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            He blessed them each according to his blessing.</l>
                        <l n="29">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            he commanded them, and said to them, ‘I will be gathered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            to my people. Bury me next to my fathers in the cave that is in the field
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            of Ephron, the Hittite.</l>
                        <l n="30">In the cave that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            is in the field of Machpelah, which is before Mamre, in the land of Canaan,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            where Abraham bought the field from Ephron, the Hittite,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            for a possession as a sepulchre.</l>
                        <l n="31">There they buried
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            Abraham and Sarah, his wife, there they buried
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            Isaac and Rebekah, his wife, and there I buried
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            Leah.</l>
                        <l n="32">The purchase of the field and of the cave
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            that is in it was from the children of Heth.’</l>
                        <l n="33">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            Jacob finished commanding his sons, and he gathered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            his feet into the bed, and rested, and was gathered
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Gen049-P85r-L15_trl" n="15" next="ADub.III.73.001.trl.050.xml#Gen050-P85r-L15_trl" />
                            to his people.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
